text.section:
Application for placement of a child or adolescent in a private therapeutic group home may be made under this section by:
An individual who is 16 years old or older;
A parent or guardian on behalf of the child or adolescent;
With the consent of the parent or guardian of the child or adolescent, a psychiatrist or psychologist who treats the child or adolescent;
On behalf of a child or adolescent, a local department of social services that has custody or guardianship of the child or adolescent under § 3-819 of the Courts Article;
The Department of Education or the local education agency with the consent of a parent or guardian;
On behalf of a child or adolescent, the Department of Juvenile Services when the Department has custody or guardianship of the child or adolescent under § 3-819 of the Courts Article; or
The circuit court of a county sitting as the juvenile court.

A private therapeutic group home may not accept an individual under this section unless:
The individual is under the age of 18 years;
The individual has a mental disorder;
The individual, because of the mental disorder, requires residential services not available in the home;
The individual needs 24-hour supervision in a structured private therapeutic group home;
The individual is or should be receiving treatment for the mental disorder; and
There is no less restrictive form of treatment that is consistent with the welfare and safety of the child or adolescent.
